I want to start by saying, I am okay. I am here to bring awareness to things not always seen. 

Auto Immune 
hormone imbalancement
PCOS
lupus
anxiety
the list is of invisible diseases are mile long. 

All are invisible to the eye, but felt within.

IM SO PROUD OF MYSELF 🖤

One year ago today I decided to put all my fears, doubts, and worries aside and start the business I had watched for two years. 

I was familiar with social selling from the previous brand partnerships I had done in the past, but I came from a stylist background where this wasn't how hair care was sold. I was set in my ways and not open to change. 

It wasn't until I personally a stylist who had used "salon" quality products for 12 years needed help with my own hair that I became open to the idea of Monat. I quickly fell in love with the products, and from there it was a no brainer for me. 

I then began to realize all the companies I was sharing in exchange for gifting was social selling. The lightbulb went off 
for me. This was my vessel to get me where I want to go, and I got to do it with my babies by my side. Sharing products I actually used daily, and products I truly loved. 

I saw stay at home moms, college girls, girls of all walks of life making a way for themselves. 

So I got out of my own way and started my business. It may not be for everyone, sure people still talk down to network marketing companies, but I no longer care because I have found passion and peace in my journey! Our family was poisoned with jet fuel when thousands of gallons of jet fuel was knowingly leaked into our homes water by the military while living in Hawaii. 

The water leaked slowly the entire time we were living in our home until the leak became so severe that it became public knowledge when our home smelled like an auto body shop, and our water lite on fire with a match. 

The health problems still exist and the future is unknown. What this taught me is our environment is not safe. 

This is why I share the stuff I do, the non toxic swaps the safer options. You water may not have jet fuel in your water but environmental toxins are present some ways i've learned to make your home less toxic. 

👇🏻👇🏻

- get your water tested, and get a water filter (over the counter water filter, or a whole house water system.)
- get a shower and bath filter 
- get a medical grade air purifier for your home
- start eliminating toxins from your home 
- get rid of all fragrances 
- check your air vents and keep them cleaned regularly 

Toxins are everywhere you can't control that, but you can control which are in your home 🙏🏼

What are ways you limit environmental toxicity in your life?! 👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻
